    <string name="dialog_help_game">How to Play</string>
    <string name="dialog_help_game_text_1">The map is composed of interconnected stars.</string>
    <string name="dialog_help_game_text_2">The first step is to select the star you want to begin with.</string>
    <string name="dialog_help_game_text_3">Each player starts with 5 units placed in the initial star.</string>
    <string name="dialog_help_game_text_4">In each turn, each player has 2 moves.</string>
    <string name="dialog_help_game_text_5">To move units, select the source star and then select the target star where you want to move your units to.</string>
    <string name="dialog_help_game_text_6">The target star has to be connected with the source star.</string>
    <string name="dialog_help_game_text_7">If the target star is valid, select the number of units to move.</string>
    <string name="dialog_help_game_text_8">If the target star is unoccupied, the moved units will conquer it with no resistance.</string>
    <string name="dialog_help_game_text_9">If the target star belongs to an enemy, a battle will take place.</string>
    <string name="dialog_help_game_text_10">Each star can be occupied by only one player and can contain up to 9 of that player\&apos;s units.</string>
    <string name="dialog_help_game_text_11">At the end of each turn, each star which is linked to 2 or more of the same player\&apos;s stars will gain an extra unit.</string>
    <string name="dialog_help_game_text_12">Press</string>
    <string name="dialog_help_game_text_13">to pass the turn.</string>
    <string name="dialog_help_game_text_14">The game ends when you defeat all the units of your enemies.</string>
    
